Hi!

We&#39;re using Heritrix from within a large distributed system, and I&#39;m
seeing a rather strange behaviour from Heritrix here.  Using an
order.xml and seeds.txt file that works file standalone, Heritrix stops
of its own accord after just a few URLs harvested.  It does not give any
explanations or stack traces, our StatusListener merely gets the message
&quot;Finished&quot;.  Our method for starting Heritrix is shown below.  The final
log message does not appear until after Heritrix has shut down nicely,
as shown in the attached log excerpt.  order.xml and seeds.txt also
attached, feel free to try a harvest with it.  What kinds of events
could cause Heritrix to suddenly give up the spirit like that?

Thanks,
-Lars

    synchronized public void doOneCrawl() throws IOFailure {

        try {
            FileUtils.copyFile(orderfile, temporderfile);
            FileUtils.copyFile(seedsfile, tempseedsfile);
            setupOrderfile();
          } catch (IOException e){
            throw new IOFailure(&quot;Could not set up order-files&quot;,e);
          }

        XMLSettingsHandler handler = null;
        try {
            handler = new XMLSettingsHandler(temporderfile);
        } catch (InvalidAttributeValueException e) {
            throw new IOFailure(&quot;Not valid order.xml-file&quot;,e);
        }
        handler.initialize();
        crawlController = new CrawlController();
        try {
            crawlController.initialize(handler);
        } catch
(org.archive.crawler.framework.exceptions.InitializationException e) {
            throw new IOFailure(&quot;Could not initialize Heritrix
CrawlController&quot;,e);
        }
        crawlController.addCrawlStatusListener(new
SimpleCrawlStatusListener());
        logger.fine(&quot;Starting crawl..&quot;);
        crawlController.requestCrawlStart();
        synchronized (this) {
            try {
                wait(); // wait for the crawl to finish
            } catch (InterruptedException e) {
                throw new IOFailure(&quot;Heritrix process interrupted&quot;,e);
            }
        }
        logger.fine(&quot;Ending crawl..&quot;);
    }


